# Frontend — React Rules

Use component-based architecture.

- Use **functional components** only (no class components)
- Use **hooks** for logic; separate UI from business logic
- Keep components small and reusable
- **Maximum component size: 200 lines**
- Prefer named exports over default exports

## Structure

```
components/
hooks/
services/
utils/
```

Extract custom hooks for reusable logic.

Colocate styles with components when possible.

Avoid inline styles; use Tailwind or CSS modules.

## Hooks and state
- Follow Rules of Hooks; keep hooks focused; use correct dependency arrays; cleanup in useEffect when needed
- Prefer useState for local state, useReducer for complex logic; keep state close to usage; avoid prop drilling
- Use memoization (useMemo, useCallback) and React.memo for expensive components; avoid unnecessary re-renders

## Forms and errors
- Use controlled components; validate forms; show loading/error states; use Error Boundaries and user-friendly messages

## Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML, ARIA where needed, keyboard navigation, and proper alt text for images.
